Despite the drop in prices of petrol and diesel in September, Nigerians paid more for transport fare in September than in August, 2019. The transport fare watch report for September 2019 released by the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) showed that average fare paid by commuters for bus journey within the city increased by 0.34 per cent month-on-month and by 1.93 per cent year-on-year to N189.05 in September 2019 from N188.41 in August 2019. States with highest bus journey fares within city were Zamfara (N320), Cross River (N305) and Abuja FCT (N289) while states with lowest bus journey fares within city were Sokoto (N138), Anambra (N138) and Bauchi (N105). OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Similarly, the average fare paid by commuters for bus journey intercity increased by 0.15 per cent month-on-month and decreased by -10.28 per cent year-on-year to N1,627.27 in September 2019 from N1,624.76 in August 2019. States with highest bus journey fares intercity were Abuja FCT (N4,168), Adamawa (N2,537) and Borno (N2,455) while states with lowest bus journey fares within city were Bayelsa (N997), Bauchi (N959) and Enugu (N955). Meanwhile, within the same period, the average price paid by consumers for automotive gas oil (diesel) decreased by -0.50 per cent month-on-month and increased by 7.69 per cent year-on-year to N227.92 in September 2019 from to N229.08 in August 2019. States with the highest average price of diesel were Borno (N271), Niger (N253.75) and Taraba (N252.60) while states with the lowest average price of diesel were Ekiti (N200.33), Rivers (N208) and Bayelsa (N208.33). Similarly, the average price paid by consumers for Premium Motor Spirit (petrol) decreased by -1.2 per cent year-on-year and flat month-on-month to N145.5 in September 2019 from N145.5 in August 2019. States with the highest average price of PMS (petrol) were Cross River (N147.50), Benue (N147.17) and Bayelsa (N146.75) while states with the lowest average price of PMS (petrol) were Abuja (N143.17), Bauchi (N144) and Kaduna (N144.13).  Abuja, Adamawa, Borno top states with highest bus fares - NBS Bauchi residents paid lowest bus fare in January â€” NBS ...Transport fares soar